Service Requests can be submitted for yourself or on behalf of another person. Service Requests are reviewed by the function receiving them and turned into Work Orders once approved

Service Requests can be submitted for yourself or on behalf of another person. Service Requests are reviewed by the function receiving them and turned into Work Orders once approved. You have the option of automatically receiving key status notifications for any Service Request that you create. Common uses for Service Requests are: - · Requesting environmental services (EMS) or (EPS) support to clean a patient room - · Issuing a request to logistics (PPM) to turn in an Asset - · Requesting repairs on plumbing or electrical systems from Facilities Management (FM) - · Reporting malfunctioning biomedical Assets (HTM) NOTE: Individuals creating Service Requests in Maximo are the same individuals who created Work Requests in AEMS/MERS. As you learned in the Service Request Overview module, you can create a new Service Request in Maximo by: - · Selecting the New Service Request link in the Quick Insert portlet on your Start Center .

As you learned in the Service Request Overview module, you can create a new Service Request in Maximo by: - · Selecting the New Service Request link in the Quick Insert portlet on your Start Center . Figure 1. Favorite Applications - New Service Request Link NOTE: You may also select Go To > Self Service>Service Requests>Create Service Request from the Navigation Bar. When the New Service Request page opens, make sure you fill out the necessary fields. Remember that an asterisk (*) next to a field indicates a required field. All required fields should be filled out before you can submit your Service Request for approval. The Create Service Request Job Aid outlines the steps for creating the following types of Service Requests. - · Basic Service Request for an Asset or Location - · Asset Turn In Service Request - · Report of Survey (ROS) Survey Service Request - · Special Event (Set Up) Service Request NOTE: The Job Aid can be found using this link to the EAWM Maximo Training

· Asset Turn In Service Request - · Report of Survey (ROS) Survey Service Request - · Special Event (Set Up) Service Request NOTE: The Job Aid can be found using this link to the EAWM Maximo Training & Project Resource Site: http://vaww.infoshare.va.gov/sites/vhaspt/projectresource/End%20User%20Resource%2 0Documents/Forms/Job_Aids.aspx Figure 2. Create Service Request - Required Fields If you are reporting the Service Request for someone else, you must change the Affected Person field. When entering the name of the Affected Person , remember: - · Existing User: Search for and then select the VA Network ID or Name of the user. - · New User: If the affected person is new and has not been provisioned, their name will not be found in the Select/Value list. If you don't find the name of your affected user, you'll need to contact your Site Lead or POC to get him/her added. NOTE: If you do not know your local Functional Community POC or Site Lead, you can search for them by going to the E

NOTE: If you do not know your local Functional Community POC or Site Lead, you can search for them by going to the EAWM Maximo Training and Project Resource Site at: http://vaww.infoshare.va.gov/sites/vhaspt/projectresource/Pages/OnePage.aspx. Select Points of Contact, select your VISN and select your site to locate the appropriate contact. IMPORTANT! Remember that sensitive information, such as Internal Business Information (IBI), Personally Identifiable Information (PII), and Personally Identifiable Health Information (PHI) is NOT ALLOWED anywhere on the Service Request, attached documents, or when creating a communication. If you are unsure what the correct responsible department should be on your Service Request, please leave it blank. This way, all the communities will see the Service Request on their Start Centers and they will assign it to the appropriate department.

This way, all the communities will see the Service Request on their Start Centers and they will assign it to the appropriate department. ## Attach Documents to a Service Request As you learned in the WBT, when necessary, you can attach documents or forms to the Service Request you created. - · Remember that all attachments require storage, and that storage contributes to the recurring costs of maintaining the Maximo system. Please be judicious when scanning simple black and white documents and please compress photos to the extent that you can. Most cameras provide resolutions in excess of simple documentation needs - · Use your judgement and upload what is minimally needed to convey the information you want to attach. - · Note that .html and .htm attachments are forbidden to preclude the risks associated with these file types. Please consider using Adobe Acrobat as your primary file type, since it is resistant to tampering

html and .htm attachments are forbidden to preclude the risks associated with these file types. Please consider using Adobe Acrobat as your primary file type, since it is resistant to tampering and has good compression. WARNING! ATTACHMENTS: Avoid attaching actual documents. Store the document on a network/shared drive and attach the link to the document. When you Add New Attachments use the Add New Web Page option rather than the Add New File Option whenever possible. Attachments ## Evaluate a Service Request The Service Requestor creates a Service Request in Maximo and submits it for approval. - · If the facility has Work Order Clerks who are Maximo users, then they are the first responders to incoming requests. - · If there is no Work Order Clerk at the facility, then the Admin is the first responder to incoming requests. IMPORTANT! EPS Admins will receive an automatic notification when a new Service Request is created for the EPS Responsible Department .

ity, then the Admin is the first responder to incoming requests. IMPORTANT! EPS Admins will receive an automatic notification when a new Service Request is created for the EPS Responsible Department . The Admin or Work Order Clerk evaluates the Service Request: - · If the Service Request is valid, the Admin, Supervisor, or Work Order Clerk needs to determine whether or not planning is required and then route the workflow in order to generate the Work Order in Maximo. If the Service Request is invalid, the Admin or Work Order Clerk needs to disapprove it, which is what we will learn next. ## Disapprove a Service Request If the Service Request is not valid, the Admin or Work Order Clerk disapproves the Service Request in Maximo, which ends the process. Here are the steps on how this is done: - Step 1. From the Start Center , select Service Requests in the Favorite Applications portlet. The Service Requests application opens with the List tab selected.

From the Start Center , select Service Requests in the Favorite Applications portlet. The Service Requests application opens with the List tab selected. - Step 2. On the List tab, to search for the Service Request enter information into one or more Filter Fields , or put your cursor in the Service Request field and press Enter and a list of all Service Requests will display. Select the Service Request you wish to disapprove (Reject). The Service Request opens on the Service Request tab. Figure 4. Service Requests Application - Log Tab - New Row Step 3. Select the Log tab. Add a new log stating why you are disapproving the Service Request by selecting the New Row button. Figure 5. Service Requests Application - Log Tab - Step 4. Enter a short reason for disapproval in both the Summary field and if necessary, a more detailed reason in the Details free-form text area. Figure 6. Log Tab - Summary and Details - Step 5.

Enter a short reason for disapproval in both the Summary field and if necessary, a more detailed reason in the Details free-form text area. Figure 6. Log Tab - Summary and Details - Step 5. Select the Change Status icon in the toolbar. Step 6. When changing the status of a Service Request to Rejected , enter a reason into the Memo field. This information will be included in a communication back to the Service Requester. Figure 7. Enter Memo Before Rejecting SR ## Step 7. Change the status of the Service Request to REJECTED . Figure 8. Change Status - Rejected Note: This status and Memo information will be included in a communication back to the Service Requester. ## Step 8. Select OK . Some common reasons why Service Requests are disapproved: - · There is a duplicate of another Service Request (this is the most common reason why a Service Request is disapproved) - · Someone calls and indicates errors on the Service Request.
